    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on the seven assessed factors and the Monte Carlo UQ coverage, noting that the decision consequence is high but that the achieved levels are considered sufficient for the current regulatory submission stage. Re-validation of model inputs against the 2026-02-01 model revision using updated boundary condition data is planned for the next assessment cycle. The team acknowledged that the primary boundary condition dataset (dataVintage 2025-09-15) predates the model revision but judged the geometric changes to be minor and unlikely to materially alter inlet/outlet conditions. This judgement has not been formally substantiated.",
